  "prompt": "What are the best contributions of india to the world in all fields?",
  "response": "India has made significant contributions to the world across various fields, including science and technology, arts and culture, spirituality, economics, and more. Here are some noteworthy contributions:\n\n### Science and Technology:\n1. **Mathematics**: \n   - **Zero**: The concept of zero as a number was first developed by ancient Indian mathematicians.\n   - **Decimal System**: The decimal system based on the number 10 was also developed in India.\n   - **Trigonometry**: Indian mathematicians like Aryabhata and Bhaskara made significant contributions to trigonometry.\n   \n2. **Astronomy**:\n   - **Heliocentric Theory**: Early Indian astronomers suggested theories that were later validated as part of the heliocentric model.\n   - **Calculations of Planetary Motions**: Ancient texts like \"Aryabhatiya\" by Aryabhata include detailed calculations related to planetary motions.\n\n3. **Medicine**:\n   - **Ayurveda**: One of the oldest systems of medicine in the world, which emphasizes holistic health and well-being.\n   - **Surgery**: Ancient texts describe complex surgeries, including rhinoplasty (reconstructive surgery for the nose).\n\n4. **Computing**: \n   - **Algorithm Development**: Indian mathematician and computer scientist Raj Reddy contributed to artificial intelligence and algorithms.\n\n### Arts and Culture:\n1. **Literature**:\n   - **Epics**: \"Mahabharata\" and \"Ramayana\" are ancient epics that have influenced storytelling globally.\n   - **Poetry and Prose**: Contributions from Rabindranath Tagore, who won the Nobel Prize in Literature.\n\n2. **Music and Dance**:\n   - **Classical Music**: Development of ragas and talas, which have influenced global music traditions.\n   - **Dance**: Classical dance forms like Bharatanatyam, Kathak, and Odissi.\n\n3. **Film**:\n   - **Bollywood**: One of the largest and most influential film industries in the world, known for its unique style and storytelling.\n\n### Philosophy and Spirituality:\n1. **Yoga**: Originating in ancient India, yoga has become a global practice promoting physical and mental well-being.\n2. **Meditation**: Techniques developed in India are used worldwide to promote mindfulness and stress relief.\n3. **Indian Philosophy**: Schools of thought like Vedanta, including influential texts like the Upanishads and Bhagavad Gita.\n\n### Economics and Commerce:\n1. **Trade**: The historic Silk Road facilitated trade routes where India played a central role.\n2. **Management**: Contributions in modern business practices and leadership.\n\n### Social Contributions:\n1. **Non-violent Resistance**: Mahatma Gandhi's philosophy of non-violence and civil disobedience inspired global movements for social justice and freedom.\n\n### Environmental Contributions:\n1. **Sustainable Practices**: Traditional Indian agricultural practices emphasize sustainability and ecological balance.\n\n### Intellectual Contributions:\n1. **Nalanda University**: One of the oldest universities in the world, attracting students from various countries.\n\nThese contributions from India have been instrumental in shaping global practices and philosophies, influencing a wide array of sectors worldwide.",
